# TTS Server API Keys Configuration
#
# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to api_keys.txt (or any location)
# 2. Add one API key per line
# 3. Lines starting with # are comments and will be ignored
# 4. Empty lines are ignored
#
# If you use a custom location, set the TTS_API_KEY_FILE environment variable:
#   export TTS_API_KEY_FILE=/path/to/your/api_keys.txt
#
# Default search locations (in order):
#   1. ./api_keys.txt (current directory)
#   2. ~/.tts-server/api_keys.txt (user home directory)
#   3. /etc/tts-server/api_keys.txt (system-wide)
#
# Example keys (replace with your own secure random keys):

your-secret-key-here
another-api-key-123abc
production-key-xyz789

# Generate secure random keys with:
# openssl rand -hex 32
# or
# uuidgen
